{
  "stem": "8610.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In this respect, I was British, I had a British commission, and I had 25,000 Hebrew-speaking Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Because of the political frustrations that these men suffered, I was looked upon by them, by many of them, as being a representative of the-- of the establishment, to which they took great exception.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The British, on the other hand, used to say I'm the spokesman of the Palestinians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I was between the hammer and the anvil.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But, on the other hand, I had excellent relations with some of the leading figures of Palestine, as it then was.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Moshe Shertok who became Moshe Sharett, was a-- became a very close friend.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I could talk to him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I had a few very old friends from, from my early days serving in the Jewish agency.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I had people to whom I could talk, particularly on the political issues.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we were faced with a number of problems because it was still the period of British mandate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Jews wanted to fight Hitler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they weren't given the chance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the late Dr.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Weizmann, for example, said he could raise a division of Jews, who were ready to serve.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the answer he got was, we haven't the means of equipping them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That was an excuse.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And this is the sort of thing that happened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was trying to maintain the balance between Jews and Arabs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, Arabs were supposed to serve as well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were given the opportunity of serving.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they, unfortunately-- and it very often happened-- you'd give them a rifle, and they would disappear with the rifle.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they were trained with a broom handles.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
